President Obama is set to travel to Nevada, New Mexico, Oklahoma, and Ohio to highlight his administration's energy strategy. This includes expanding responsible oil and gas development, increasing fuel economy, supporting renewable energy sources, and investing in infrastructure and research and development. The President will visit the Copper Mountain Solar 1 Facility in Nevada to highlight the focus on diversifying the energy portfolio. He will also visit oil and gas production fields in New Mexico and discuss the commitment to expanding domestic oil and gas production. In Oklahoma, he will discuss improving and supporting infrastructure, including a pipeline that will transport oil from Cushing to the Gulf of Mexico. The final stop will be at Ohio State University to showcase advanced energy-related research and development.